32:16.000 --> 32:22.000
Then I came back and Herman Daly introduced me to Josh Farley, who you know.

32:22.000 --> 32:30.000
Josh and John Erickson were my PhD advisors along with Robert Costanza at University of Vermont.

32:30.000 --> 32:33.000
That broadened out my awareness.

32:33.000 --> 32:36.000
It's not just energy. It's not just oil.

32:36.000 --> 32:38.000
It's human behavior.

32:38.000 --> 32:45.000
It's aggregate anthropological momentum of the human superorganism.

32:45.000 --> 32:52.000
I became really intellectually curious about how all this stuff fit together.

32:52.000 --> 32:58.000
I became a contributor on the oil drum and eventually co-ran the oil drum,

32:58.000 --> 33:02.000
which was an interesting model because we had over 30 PhDs

33:02.000 --> 33:07.000
that were volunteering their time for the greater social good to share information.

33:07.000 --> 33:13.000
It was a neat little cafe sandbox of intellectual collaboration for a while.

33:13.000 --> 33:21.000
