33:21.000 --> 33:29.000
I approached Homeland Security looking at how we would buttress our supply chains

33:29.000 --> 33:36.000
if there was a Minsky moment where we realized we weren't able to service our debt.

33:36.000 --> 33:39.000
So more Minsky than the housing market?

33:39.000 --> 33:43.000
Yeah. Minsky with a capital M.

33:43.000 --> 33:48.000
Do you want to just explain because some people might not know what Minsky moment means?

33:48.000 --> 33:56.000
A Minsky moment is where you can no longer solve a credit crisis by adding more credit.

33:56.000 --> 34:05.000
It's the moment where everyone recognizes what's happening and there's an exodus

34:05.000 --> 34:11.000
and you can't solve the thing by adding more credit because there's no trust there.

34:11.000 --> 34:18.000
Right now, the markets are approaching new highs and people are still dancing

34:18.000 --> 34:25.000
because the credit spigot is still on, but they're dancing closer to the doors in talking with them.

34:25.000 --> 34:31.000
But anyways, getting back to your question, which I'm giving way too long winded of an answer,

34:31.000 --> 34:43.000
I then started realizing that the people in middle age between 25 and 60 have no bandwidth

34:43.000 --> 34:48.000
because their status and identity were attached to the jobs and the positions they were in.

34:48.000 --> 34:54.000
In this story, the great simplification, which wasn't fully formed back then,

34:54.000 --> 34:59.000
was too abstract and threatening to their current work.

34:59.000 --> 35:07.000
